Of an involuntary preference to
her cou&s;in, &s;he had been &s;en&s;ible from the
fir&s;t moment &s;he &s;aw him; and his indif|ference,
his preference of Cele&s;tina, and
even his po&s;itively declining the honour of
her hand, had mortified without curing her
