&s;eriou&s;ly intend to marry."</P>
<P><PB N="217" REF="227">
So acute was the pain which the intelli|gence
Willoughby had ju&s;t received gave
him, that he could make no an&s;wer to this;
and Jarvis fancying him out of &s;pirits for
&s;ome rea&s;on or other which he never
thought of enquiring after, &s;oon after left
