<P>There was "room for meditation even
"to madne&s;s," when he recollected a thou|&s;and
circum&s;tances that had till now ap|peared
of no moment; he was convinced
that Vava&s;our had long admired Cele&s;tina;
he had him&s;elf re&s;igned her, or at lea&s;t in|timated
that he dared not think of her;
