<P>He was concerned, however, for his un|cle,
and returned in the evening to take
leave of him: he found him &s;itting with
Mrs. Calder, who was reading to him a
&s;ort of <HI>catalogue rai&s;onn&eacute;e</HI> of the various ills
to which the human body is &s;ubject; and as
