<P>On her entrance, Willoughby &s;at down
again, as being unwilling to have her
&s;uppo&s;e he rudely fled from her approach.
She put on an air of affected humility, and
looked as if &s;he thanked him for even this
&s;light mark of attention. She gave a loud
and deep &s;igh, prolonged as much as po&s;|&s;ible;
her eyes, robbed of their fire, were
